<h3>Pulses : Importance&nbsp;</h3>
<p>Sustainability + rain fed agri and SM farmer;s income&nbsp;+ nutrition&nbsp;</p>
<p>pulse production increased by48% in past 10 years&nbsp;</p>
<h4>sustainability&nbsp;</h4>
<p>(legumes = N fixation and water conserve)</p>
<h4>Rain fed agri (as per Rainfed Agri Atlas )</h4>
<ol>
<li><strong>Rainfed agriculture = 60% of value of agri GDP&nbsp;</strong></li>
<li>88% of pulses production from rainfed areas</li>
<li>these lands support 75% of sheep , 65% cattle.</li></ol>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<h3>Changing pulses to more remunerative model&nbsp;</h3>
<ol>
<li>INFRA = Agro processing clusters under SAMPADA</li>
<li>FUNDING =&nbsp;AIF worth 1L cr.&nbsp;</li>
<li>VALUE ADDITION = processed cost &gt;&gt; raw pulses</li>
<li>CONVERGENCE = NRLM and SHGs&nbsp;</li>
<li>DECENTRALISED = PM FPO promotion = 10k new FPOs by 2023-2024</li>
<li>ENTREPRENEURSHIP = agri-business and startup tax incentive e.g. <em><strong>Innovation and Agri entrep. Dev. Prog. under RKVY</strong></em></li>
<li>CONTRACT FARMING for better price realisation of raw produce.</li>
<li><span style="color:#2ecc71">price stabilisation fund and ECA reforms (pvt invest in agri value chain)</span></li></ol>